args: All right, children. Let us sing.
Lift your voices to the Goddess's ears.\nSing her praises in love and in joy!
How about a hymn of confession instead?
Oh, hello, Faris.\nWhat's this about confession?
For your part in the disappearance of\nchildren from this very orphanage.
Goodness. I'm afraid I have no\nidea what you mean.
We found the secret door to the hidden\nroom in your chambers, ma'am.
And the records of your transactions\nwith a certain organization inside it.
You raised talented children, then\nsold them off for a colossal sum.
What are they after?\nWhy are they gathering gifted children?
Ha ha. I have no idea.\nAbout any of this.
I find that hard to believe.\nI have proof right here!
That's simply proof of my love, child.
I don't care in the slightest who that\norganization is or what they're after.\nI couldn't possibly care less.
I just wanted to prove my love.\nI wanted it seen. Recognized.
One thing I can say for certain...\nThis all started with you, Faris.
You were so bright. Do you have any idea\nhow happy I was the day you were taken in\nby the academy at Church Headquarters?
Faris is an exceptionally gifted child.
I'm certain the true love you nurtured\nhim with cultivated the soil for his myriad\ntalents to take seed.
You can't imagine how happy those words\nmade me. How proud...
I gave, and I gave, and I gave...\nand in the end, I had nothing left.
Such is the fate of an orphanage caretaker.\nBut that time was different!
My love was recognized.\nTRUE love, he called it!
I needed to show more people the strength\nof my love. Needed to use that rarefied\nlove to help my children's talents blossom.
Just like they had with you.
So you sold off the most talented children.\nWhat about the others?
If you wish a rose to bloom to its fullest,\nit must be pruned. The same principle\napplies. Heh. Perfectly logical, isn't it?
We are apostles:\nthe executors of Ilia's will.
Your twisted expression of love ends here,\nMother. You're coming with us.
Yeah! It was those kids' fault for not doing\nas they were told!
Why are you being mean to Mother?
She's not the bad guy...\nYOU people are the bad guys!
That isn't true! We're here to save you!
Oh, bless you, my precious darlings...
Do you see now? You speak of the\nGoddess's will and break these\nchildren's hearts in the same breath.
As someone who grew up here, surely\nyou can see the cruelty in your actions.
(Faris knows better than anyone how\nthese kids feel.)
(The drive to work hard to make a parent\nproud... The hunger for approval...)
(Faris loved her.\nI'm sure he feels conflicted.)
(So I have to be the one to step up. There\nhas to be some way to get her to turn\nherself in without scarring these children!)
I don't want to fight with you, Faris.\nWe're family. We don't need words\nto understand each other, do we?
Come to Mother, child. Let me hold you in\nmy arms and we can lay this all to rest.
(She was planning to feign a hug and\ngo for the kill!)
And you, children. Lay the weapons\nyou're hiding on the floor beside you.
Even if you tried to use them, you wouldn't\nstop us, and it won't bring Mother back.
(She gave weapons to the kids?\nAnd he knew it from the start...)
She was all I had...\nMother was the only family I had!
No matter how hard it got, I could always\nbe strong and get through it for her sake.
She was everything to me!\nWhy did you kill her?! WHYYYYY?!
(The screams of sobbing children, met only\nwith Faris's cold stare...and beside him,\nthe remains of what was once his mother.)
(This place is far from paradise.\nIt is a vision of hell itself.)
